# Fix Floorplan Parsing Bugs (Graph Builder + Detection Integration)

The floorplan parsing pipeline works on MP-860-3L.png (63-room office plan) but produces an **all-zero adjacency matrix**, meaning graph has nodes but no edges. YOLO detection itself works (65 doors, 194 walls, 41 windows). The root cause is a critical indentation bug in [graph_builder.py](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/floorparsing/Agentic/graph_builder.py) that corrupts the isolated-node repair logic, plus missing room coordinates preventing spatial door-room association.

## Proposed Changes

### Graph Builder — Indentation + Logic Fix

#### [MODIFY] [graph_builder.py](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/floorparsing/Agentic/graph_builder.py)

**Bug**: Lines 380-396 in [_repair_isolated_nodes](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/floorparsing/Agentic/graph_builder.py#241-412) have completely broken indentation. The current code is:

```python
for j in range(n):
    if j == idx:
if best_j is None:          # ← wrongly at same level as for-loop
    for j in range(n):       # ← unreachable / wrong scope
        if j != idx and j not in isolated:
            best_j = j
            break

            continue          # ← dead code
        other_cent = _room_centroid(rooms[j])  # ← dead code
        if room_cent and other_cent:
            d = _euclidean(room_cent, other_cent)
            if d < best_dist:
                best_dist = d
                best_j = j
```

**Fix**: Restore proper indentation so Strategy 3 (centroid proximity) actually iterates rooms, computes distances, and picks the nearest. The fallback (connect to next sequential room) should only trigger after the loop completes with no result:

```python
        for j in range(n):
            if j == idx:
                continue
            other_cent = _room_centroid(rooms[j])
            if room_cent and other_cent:
                d = _euclidean(room_cent, other_cent)
                if d < best_dist:
                    best_dist = d
                    best_j = j

        if best_j is None:
            # No coordinates available — connect to next sequential room
            for j in range(n):
                if j != idx and j not in isolated:
                    best_j = j
                    break
```

---

### No Other Files Modified

YOLO detection ([detection.py](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/floorparsing/detection.py)) is confirmed working. The [_detect_local](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/floorparsing/detection.py#295-330) function correctly finds 65 doors, 194 walls, 41 windows on the test image. No changes needed there.

The parser agent, orchestrator, models, and CLI code are all structurally sound. The all-zero adjacency matrix in [graph.json](file:///c:/Tim/AIDGPT/AidGPT/results/graph.json) is a downstream symptom — the LLM may have returned edges but the graph builder's repair couldn't fix isolated nodes due to the indentation bug.

